related_questions.question: What is a cell that converts solar energy to electricity?
related_questions.snippet: Solar cells, also called photovoltaic cells, are the building blocks of solar panels. Solar cells are made of semiconductor materials like silicon that produce a "photoelectric effect" when exposed to sunlight. The photoelectric effect occurs when sunlight knocks electrons loose from their atoms.
